            "text": "1st Division of Gastroenterology, Fondazione IRCCS Ca' Granda, Ospedale Maggiore Policlinico, Universit a di Milano, Milan, Italy. E-mail: pietro.lampertico@unimi.it doi:10.1111/apt.12615 SIRS, St\u20ac attermayer et al. 1 reported on the accuracy of the recently discovered interferon-k4 (IFNL4) ss469415590 variant (TT or DG) in conjunction with the two widely studied interleukin 28B (IL28B) single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs), rs12979860 and rs8099917, for predicting the likelihood of a response to pegylated IFN-a-2a (PEG) and ribavirin (RBV) in a large set (n.754) of chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV) patients.",
